<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861219-0176 </DOCNO><HL> Geothermal ResourcesTo Buy Magma StakeIn Power Plant, Rights</HL><DD> 12/19/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GEO MAGE MGMATENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> SAN MATEO, Calif.  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Geothermal Resources International Inc. said it agreed in principle to buy the interests in a power plant, plus related development rights and electricity supply contracts, of Magma Power Co. and a unit.    All three companies develop geothermal energy.    Under terms, Geothermal will pay Magma Power and its Magma Energy Inc. as much as a total of $15 million for interests in the B.C. McCabe power plant in the Imperial Valley of Southern California; development rights to geothermal resources on lands adjacent to the plant; and two long-term electricity sales contracts with Southern California Edison Co., a Rosemead, Calif., utility, for the area.    Magma Power and Magma Energy would retain an interest in electricity revenue from the existing and any future power plants, Geothermal said. The interest wasn't specified.    Geothermal expects to execute definitive agreements, subject to a number of conditions, by Jan. 31. </TEXT></DOC>